article.headline: Winston-Salem 56, Bethune-Cookman 48
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Darius Floyd scored 17 points and Jamal Durham added 16 as Winston-Salem beat Bethune-Cookman 56-48 on Saturday. Winston-Salem(4-19), which has won three of its last four games, never trailed. Bethune-Cookman (4-14, 2-7 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who were plagued by poor shooting throughout the game, were led by Jimmy Hudson's 17 points. Floyd hit five three-pointers and Durham also contributed by claiming a game-high 12 rebounds. Winston-Salem jumped to a 17-4 lead at the start of the game, thanks to five early 3-pointers -- three of them from Floyd. Bethune-Cookman hit only one of its first 15 shots in the game's first ten minutes, enabling Winston-Salem to take control. Winston-Salem, whose lead was double-figures most of the way, pushed to an 18-point advantage, 46-28, with 13:14 to play. Bethune-Cookman then went on a 15-2 run to close the margin to five points, 48-43, with 3:25 on the clock. But Winston-Salem wouldn't allow them to close the gap any further.
